      <h2 style="font-weight:700;font-family:Open Sans;color:#01498B;margin:3px 0 0 0;">Erin Mulberg</h2>
      <h3 style="font-weight:300;text-transform:uppercase;font-family:'museo-sans';color:#008FB4;margin:3px 0 15px 0;">Project Coordinator</h3>
      <div class="profile" style="color:#676767;font-size:16px;letter-spacing:0.5px;"><p>Based in Brightworks’ Bay Area office in Oakland, CA, Erin Mulberg is experienced in implementing public and private sector environmental initiatives. Her areas of expertise include:</p>
<ul>
<li>LEED EB:O+M</li>
<li>LEED Volume</li>
<li>ENERGY STAR Reporting</li>
<li>Corporate Reporting</li>
<li>GRESB</li>
<li>Energy Efficiency Incentives</li>
</ul>
<p>Before Brightworks, Erin worked as an energy and sustainability analyst within the operations division of Vornado Realty Trust, where she held responsibilities for the trust’s New York portfolio. This included analysis for a comprehensive program to improve the sustainability performance of a 20-million-square-foot real estate portfolio of commercial and retail space and management of a LEED EB:O+M Volume certification program for a portfolio of 25 buildings. She also conducted work for the trust’s ENERGY STAR, GRESB (Global Real Estate Sustainability Benchmark), and GRI (Global Reporting Initiative) reporting programs.</p>
<p>She also has experience managing energy efficiency incentive applications to finance energy efficiency projects. She then performed follow-up measurement and verification of resulting energy savings.</p>
<p>Before joining Vornado, she held positions with New York’s Urban Green Council, HR&amp;A Advisors, Honeywell Building Solution, the California Air Resources Board, and the City of Palo Alto.</p>
 </div>
